title: Iran controversy brews over girl in coma, possible victim of veil enforcement
description: The incident recalls the death in custody a year ago of Mahsa Amini over Islamic dress code violations, which sparked months of protests in Iran.

title: Russian missile attack in Kharkiv region overwhelmingly killed civilians
description: Morgue workers said they had seen no evidence of multiple military personnel among the dead and that most victims appeared to be older.

title: 2023 Nobel Peace Prize winner is Narges Mohammadi, Iranian activist
description: Imprisoned Narges Mohammadi was sentenced to 154 lashes and 10 years prison for “spreading propaganda.”

title: Biden border plan faces breakdown amid record influx of families
description: The border plan President Biden put in place months ago is at risk of collapse amid a new wave of illegal crossings, intensifying strains on U.S. cities.

title: In Australian ‘Voice’ referendum, door-knockers battle misinformation
description: A proposal to change Australia’s constitution to give Indigenous people a “Voice to Parliament” was meant to sail through. Now it looks destined to fail.

title: Israel’s embargo made donkeys critical to Gaza. Now it may take them away.
description: Donkeys are vital to commerce in Gaza, a consequence of Israel’s 15-year-old economic embargo. Now, they are increasingly hard to find, and harder to afford.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Zelensky says deadly attack is ‘absolute evil’; Biden planning major speech
description: The Russian attack on a grocery store in the village of Hroza, near Kharkiv, killed at least 51 and was one of the war’s deadliest missile strikes.

title: Chaos in Congress points to failures in the U.S. system
description: Onlookers abroad are watching an American political system lurching down the path of dysfunction and a legislature dominated by politicians uninterested in democratic deliberation.

title: Venezuela issues arrest warrant against opposition leader Juan Guaidó
description: Juan Guaidó, previously the self-declared interim president of Venezuela, escaped to the U.S. this year fleeing what he said were threats of his arrest.
